{"type": "root", "attrs": {"type": "node", "context": "sop", "internal": "labs::biome_curve_setup::1.0", "icon": "SOP/labs::biome_curve_setup::1.0", "version": "1.0", "namespace": "labs"}, "body": [{"level": 0, "type": "title", "indent": 0, "text": ["Labs Biome Curve Setup (Beta)"], "extent": [116, 150]}, {"type": "summary", "indent": 0, "text": ["This node sets the necessary attributes on curves created in Houdini to use with ", {"type": "em", "text": ["Labs Biome Initialize SOP"]}, "."], "extent": [150, 268]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["Instead of the biome interface handled through ", {"type": "em", "text": ["Labs Biome Initialize"]}, " for all other region assignment methods, this node assigns the necessary attributes to curves as they are created. The first input is the corresponding curve, and the second input is the Previous ", {"type": "em", "text": ["Biome Curve Setup"]}, " SOP in the chain. For curves that can share a biome assignment, it is possible to merge them together first before wiring into the first input."], "extent": [268, 701]}, {"level": 1, "id": "parameters", "container": true, "type": "parameters_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [701, 713], "body": [{"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "extent": [713, 720], "body": [{"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 8, "text": ["Biome Profile"], "extent": [720, 744], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 16, "text": ["Path to the biome profile JSON containing biome data such as names, parameters, etc. This data is set through the ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/labs--biome_adjust_settings", "type": "link", "text": ["Labs Biome Adjust Settings"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/labs--biome_adjust_settings.html"}, " node."], "extent": [778, 997]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "biomeprofile"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 8, "text": ["Environment Variable Set"], "exten